name: Omnium Bike Shop
directions: Through the back of the shop under the giant clock

name: Glass Onion
directions: All the way in the back around the corner.
comment: Our bathrooms do not discriminate and neither do our staff!

name: Utah Valley University Library
directions: First floor, in the entrance to the women's restroom

name: Seattle Central College - Broadway Edison Building
directions: On the 3rd floor in the Social & Human Services and Nursing department.  Right by room 3215.  Here is a link to a map: http://www.seattlecentral.edu/maps/be/3rd-floor.php
comment: You do not have to be a student to use the restrooms.

name: CVS Pharmacy
street: Wood Lake Shopping Center, 872 North Delaware Street
directions: Back left corner of the store, behind pharmacy; next to lockers
comment: Single stall, requires key from pharmacy, door is sometimes sticky; shopping center is on the border with Burlingame

name: Bianchini's Market
directions: Center back of the store, in the warehouse area; turn right
comment: Single restroom; store is across the street from post office

name: San Mateo County Human Services Agency
directions: First floor, behind the front desk, near the staff offices and conference rooms
comment: Three restrooms; at least one will not have a working soap dispenser

name: Trinity United Methodist Church
directions: Single bathrooms that are gender neutral upstairs in the middle of the building.
comment: Available Sunday mornings before and after 10:00am worship. Sometimes available during the week, ring doorbell to see if office is open.

name: Pinewood Social
directions: 3 single stalls back by the bowling

name: Whole Foods Market (Lincoln Park)
directions: There are two gender neutral family restrooms in the store. One is on the west side of the escalator (the opposite side of the bar). The other is on the mezzanine level on the far north side.
comment: There are also two single stall bathrooms in the back hallway by the meat department, but those are only accessible to team members.

name: Bowdoin College
directions: White house with Gender neutral bathrooms on the first floor
comment: This is specifically a queer friendly space.

name: Wild Goose Meeting House
directions: In the back
comment: Two neutral bathrooms intentionally created for safe space. Wonderful owners.

name: Colorado state capitol
directions: Second floor on the north end on the right -- two single stall unisex bathrooms. 3rd floor on the NW side by the gallery -- unisex accessible bathroom. Other neutral bathrooms but those are the easiest to find.
comment: The Capitol can be intimidating but it's fully public, very safe, and full of other wandering visitors so don't worry.

name: Central Texas Metropolitan Community Church
comment: Open Sunday mornings

name: Unitarian Universalist Fellowship of Waco
comment: Open Sundays 9am-1pm

name: Portfolio Coffeehouse
directions: The only restroom in the shop is gender neutral.
comment: You don't have to be a paying customer.

name: Zen Tea LLC
directions: Through the first room, first door on the left.
comment: Generally you need to be a paying customer. Prices are pretty cheap for food and tea. You could probably just say you needed a safe bathroom though.

name: Anderson Clark Center
directions: One on the first floor and one on the second floor.

name: District Cafe & Eatery
comment: Not public, customers only.

name: Caldwell park
directions: At the edge of the parking lot before you go down to the river, there is a bathroom building next to the picnic area with 2 single stall, gender neutral bathrooms

name: University of Vermont Given Building
directions: 2nd floor. at the top of the glass staircase, keep going straight- the restroom will be on your left.

name: Manchester Hall
directions: In the basement/ground floor, halfway down the hallway caddy-corner from the kitchen
comment: Knock first!

name: Four Burgers
comment: Only bathroom is single seat and gender-neutral.

name: Four Burgers
comment: Only bathroom is single seat and gender-neutral.

name: Kroger Marketplace
directions: It's right near the Little Clinic and Pharmacy.

name: Red Brick Pizza
directions: Back, to the left of the soda machine.
comment: Single room male and single room female signed bathrooms, no key needed. I'm an employee and we have no issue with anyone using either bathroom, though the men's can get stinky :P

name: Florida State University
directions: Student Disability Resource Center; 874 Traditions Way

name: Spike Island
directions: Ground floor, to the right of the gallery.
comment: maybe look at the art whilst you're there

name: Florida State University
directions: Wellness Center; Two restrooms on the fifth floor, hall way near the Administration office

name: Eat Unique
directions: It's outside the dining space. Go through the door by the drink coolers, and it's to the right
comment: Single person bathroom. Technically owned by Eat Unique, though the next door restaurant also uses it

name: Biddle's Escape
directions: Enter, walk past the counter and they're to the right, before the wall with tshirts on it
comment: Two single-person bathrooms, neither one is gendered. Always super clean!

name: Pine Centre Mall
directions: Located between Subway and Shanghai Express with a big clock over the door.
comment: It's a "family bathroom"

name: Clover Park Technical College
directions: BLDG 23 (Student Center)
comment: All restrooms are gender neutral and accessible in this building.

name: Florida State University
directions:
Strozier Library
After passing the turnstiles, walk straight towards the help desk and continue to the back wall. Restroom is on the right hand side right before the employee-only area (technically an employee restroom). Restroom is unmarked, but has a push button for opening the door.
comment:
The restroom is technically for employees, but students report using it frequently. 

You must present your FSU card or receive a guest pass for the library to enter.

name: Sushi Hut
directions: In the back behind a doorway with a decorative curtain. There's a sign that says rest rooms above it.
comment: They'd most likely want you to be a paying customer but there aren't any signs saying you have to order something. Has a braille sign on the door.

name: Gossip Grill
directions: Behind the couches/ lounge area, next to the kitchen doors

name: Willy Street Co-Op
directions: at the front of the store near the "commons" area.

name: Colorado State University Plant Sciences Building
directions: It's on the west section of the basement floor

name: Durham Language and Literature Building
directions: First floor, just north of the elevators

name: Main Stage Pizzeria
directions: in the back to the right.
comment: You don't have to be a paying customer. Just come in and ask nicely!

name: Greggs (formerly Baker's Oven)
street: Freshney Place Shopping Centre, 47 Victoria Street, DN31 1UU
directions: At the back, past the seating, through closed door and turn right
comment: Individual single room gendered toilets (one male, one female, one disabled/baby), full door, securely lockable, the men's toilet is rarely used.

name: Halifax Central Library
directions: There is a single-stall "family" bathroom located on each floor, including the ground floor. From the main entrance off Spring Garden, walk straight to the back along the left-hand wall. The single-stall washroom is between the shared, binary-gendered washrooms. The location of the three washrooms is approximately the same on each floor.
comment: The Central Library strives to be a safe, welcoming space for all people, including people of all genders. And they have no problem with people coming in just to use the washroom.

name: Union Basement
directions: enter from the basement main entrance and head toward the mailroom and take a left.
comment: you need to be a student of the college, or be associated with a group visiting the campus

name: Black Knight Games
directions: Both bathrooms are in the back of the store, right next to each other.
comment: Both bathrooms have unisex signs and are open to everyone. One is a single use, lockable room. The other has two urinals and a large stall.

name: Assemble
directions: Back behind the curtain. Ask any staff person and they'll point it out.
comment: Technically in a "non-public" part of the space but everyone is allowed to use it!

name: Shake Shack
directions: In the back, to the right

name: LGBT Welcome Center
directions: LGBTQ Community Center. All restrooms are safe and accessible.
comment: LGBTQ Community Center. All restrooms are safe and accessible.

name: Metro Wellness & Community Center
directions: LGBTQ Community Center. All restrooms are safe and accessible.
comment: LGBTQ Community Center. All restrooms are safe and accessible.

name: Metro Wellness & Community Center
directions: LGBTQ Community Center. All restrooms are safe and accessible.
comment: LGBTQ Community Center. All restrooms are safe and accessible.

name: mcclean
comment: You have to pay 2 francs.

name: Sheldon High School
directions: In main office past the vice principal secretary desk, there is a short hallway and across from the women's bathroom there is an accessible  unisex bathroom.
comment: sign that says "sick students only" but it's not usually a problem (in my experience, ive used it after school hours)

name: Pizza Rev
directions: Entering the doors, there's a hallway to the back left leading to a pair of single stall restrooms.
comment: I believe you have to be a paying customer to use them.

name: Ashland High School
directions: Gym building, outside the music area.

name: Cafe Caribe
directions: At the back of the cafe, on the left. Is down a step.
comment: This is a really small cafe, so it might feel a bit awkward to just pop in to use the toilet if there's not many customers. They people who run it and work there are really really sweet, though.

name: Kirkland's at the Antelope Valley Mall
directions: When entering Kirkland's, the restrooms are a bit hidden. You'll find the door in the back left corner of the store.
comment: Just act like your browsing and simply need to go. I someone's standing by the door, just drink some water and wait a bit. They're single stall restrooms.

name: Target
directions: Walk through the doors toward the pharmacy. It's right by the pharmacy and make-up department.
comment: Just act like you're passing by and slip in. Nothing special.

name: Sam's Club
street: 26468 Carl Boyer Drive, Santa Clarita, CA
directions: Through the doors, past the food court, and toward the pharmacy. It's the center door of the restroom area.
comment: You should have a club membership to even enter the building first.

name: Wilson Commons, University of Rochester
directions: 2nd floor

name: Humphrey Hall
directions: On the third floor near the elevators.
comment: It is accessible by both stairs and elevators. This building is a lecture hall and a research facility.

name: Target
directions: In the front by the entrance
comment: It's the family restroom

name: Target
directions: Family restroom by the front entrance

name: Grey House
directions: At the back of the house.
comment: The house is located on Queen's University campus, and there is a wheelchair accessible entrance in the back, where the bathroom is located. Normally open on business hours (Mondays-Fridays 9AM-5PM).

name: Arts Building (UOttawa)
directions: Elevator accessible. It's the fifth floor, room 513.

name: Boise state University career center
directions: On the bottom and top floor by the men's room

name: Boise state university ILC (interactive learning center)
directions: First floor only

name: Five Guys Burgers and Fries
directions: In the back there are two or three single stall gender-neutral washrooms.
comment: One of them might be labelled accessible but the surrounding area is like 90% parking lot and really hard to get to unless you have a car or you actually take one of those really obscure busses that rarely come to get there.

name: 193-195 High Street, Kew VIC 3101, Australia
directions: across the road from safeway, through a little garden
comment: also has a baby change room, is open 9am-5:330pm

name: Trenton High School
directions: Closest to the main entrance (the one with the staff parking lot), in the small highway by the phys-ed office in the foyer. The door is on the right, (I think) right before the bulletin board.
comment: This bathroom is usually the last one to lock up after hours and if you're just passing through on a weekday and don't actually go to the school, it's highly unlikely anyone will question you if you're just in to use the washroom and then get out. People staying late for afterschool activities usually will use that one. Bonus: probably the cleanest bathroom in the school.

name: Starbucks
directions: There is a family washroom beside the two gendered washrooms in the far-right corner of the coffee shop.
comment: You likely have to be a paying customer, but I've watched folks slip in the side door just to use the loo.

name: Edible Canada Bistro
street: 1596 Johnston Street near Granville Island Public Market
directions: The single stall gender-neutral washrooms are located to the left of the retail shop attached to the restaurant.
comment: Use these washrooms if you're a paying customer of the retail shop or the restaurant.

name: Urban Fare
street: 177 Davie Street between Pacific Boulevard and Marinaside Crescent
directions: Two single stall unisex washrooms are located beside the deli at the right of the store.
comment: You can use these washrooms without being a paying customer.

name: Korchma Taras Bulba
street: 357 West Broadway, New York, NY 10013, USA
directions: In the back.
comment: Sit-down restaurant with bar. Drinks are $10-14.

name: Cool Springs Galleria
directions: All bathrooms at the mall have a family restroom. One is on the second floor near Belk.

name: Bone Student Center
directions: Near information center, left of UPB office
comment: Labeled 'All Gender'

name: Trees Organic Coffee
directions: The coffee shop is on the West side of Richards Street. The single-stall gender-neutral washroom is to the left of the counter.
comment: You must be a paying customer.

name: Dawson College
directions: 2E wing and 5A wing

name: Funtastic Cards
directions: Located in back room near the bait.
comment: For gaming customers.

name: Trader Joe's Old Town
directions: Back of the store, near the greeting cards.

name: Google GWC2
directions: Behind main lobby
comment: must be a badged google employee or guest

name: Boise Bicycle Project
directions: Back of the bike shop, door has green frame. Only restroom in shop, thus gender neutral.
comment: They welcome all who bike. Pretend like you were browsing for a bit then ask.

name: Southern Rail Restaurant and Bar
directions: It's in the same hallway as the gendered restrooms (which are also single-user).
comment: I doubt you could get in unless you were a customer. As noted in the directions, all the bathrooms are single-person, with two gendered ones and a unisex one.

name: Cafe Pyrus
directions: At the back of the Cafe behind what looks like a wall, there are two single use washrooms.
comment: Queer friendly.

name: Cool Springs Galleria
directions: Second floor by Belk

name: Cool Springs Galleria
directions: Second floor by Belk

name: Cool Springs Galleria Mall
directions: On the second floor by Belk
comment: do not have to be a customer

name: Cornbread Cafe
comment: You might have to be a "paying customer". They have delicious cookies for $1-2 near the cash register.

name: Mary's Place Cafe II
directions: Washrooms are at the very back of the restaurant. There are two single-stall, neutral washrooms located on the left-hand wall.
comment: Their washrooms are generally for paying customers, but the staff is friendly to trans* and gender-nonconforming people, and may let you use them if you just ask.

name: Halifax Infirmary
directions: There are gender neutral/unisex washrooms in multiple locations throughout the building. The unisex washrooms are marked with the same symbol this app uses for its icon. They are typically single-stall.
comment: The Halifax Infirmary is the site of the local ER, as well as many other medical services. They get hundreds or thousands of people passing through the site each day. So if you walk with confidence, no one will know you're just there to use the washroom. :)

name: Robbins Library
directions: Walk past the front desk and turn right. On your left, you'll see two gender-neutral restrooms with wide wooden doors. Knock before entering.
comment: The library regularly runs programs and book clubs with an LGBTQ+ focus, so they're likely sympathetic to the need for safe restrooms. It's a wonderful library with big windows and gorgeous patterns painted on the ceiling. Pick up a book and stay for a while!

name: Parsons Fine Arts
directions: Fifth floor on the south/west side of the building.
comment: Enter with New School ID. Good place to poop. Also has a sharps container!

name: Fine Arts Building, New School University
directions: 5th Floor. When exiting the elevator, turn right, then left at the first door. At the end of the hall turn right and the bathroom is on your left, across from the computers.
comment: You have to have a New School ID, but it does depend on the security guard. This bathroom is a good place to poop since it's single stall. There is also a sharps container in there in case you need to inject hormones or insulin while you're in there!

name: Must Be Heaven
directions: Against the back wall in the main dining area, past the food counter.

name: Oh So Good
comment: Washrooms are for customers only. Safe space.
